JOHANNESBURG - As we approach New Year's Eve many people are celebrating with their families and loved ones. But some are experiencing loneliness and depression for reasons that could include divorce, retrenchment or the loss of loved ones. READ: SA mental health services neglected and underfunded Clinical psychologist Barry Viljoen said the festive season is marketed as a time to spend with family and friends leaving some people isolated due to circumstances. Viljoen mentioned the exacerbating influence of social media as people see others celebrating.